    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/133.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Having reference to the Joint Resolution of Congress approved August 9, 1912,
                    which authorized this Department to investigate claims arising on this side of
                    the Mexican border and growing out of the revolution in adjacent Mexican
                    territory, a commission for the purpose indicated has been appointed.</p>
                <p>It is understood that many of the claims in question have already been presented
                    to the Department of State, and as the early conclusion of the investigation
                    would be facilitated by any list of the claims now available, it is requested
                    that this Department be furnished with such information of the kind indicated as
                    may be on file in the Department of State, provided such action meets with your
                    approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leonard Wood.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—On September 16, 1912, President Madero read
                        his message to the Twenty-sixth Congress; in it he made references to the
                        American claims; see “Messages of the President,” <ref target="#pg_708">p.
                            708</ref>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
